#import "../../macros/category.typ": *

== Category-theory notation

The category module provides common operators for ordinary category-theory text.

$Ob(cal(C))$, $Mor(cal(C))$, $Hom_cal(C)(A, B)$, $End_cal(C)(A)$, $Aut_cal(C)(A)$, and $Nat(F, G)$.

$id_A : A -> A$, $lim F$, $colim F$, $Lan_F G$, and $Ran_F G$.

The opposite-category helper renders $opcat(cal(C))$.
